    </div>
    <div class="sofi-why">
      <div class="sofi-reason"><strong>They are us.</strong> SoFi was built for the generation that does everything on their phone — banking, investing, loans. Their customer is literally you.</div>
      <div class="sofi-reason"><strong>They got profitable.</strong> SoFi posted its first full year of net income in 2024 and raised guidance multiple times in 2025. Revenue growing ~16% per year.</div>
      <div class="sofi-reason"><strong>They have a bank charter.</strong> In 2022 SoFi became a real bank — meaning they can hold deposits and lend from them, which is far cheaper than borrowing capital. That changes their entire cost structure.</div>
      <div class="sofi-reason"><strong>The price is right for us.</strong> At ~$4–6/share, one contract controls 100 shares at a cost of $400–$600 in collateral — perfect for a $500 account. We're not using SOFI because it's our favorite stock. We're using it because it's the right size for where we are right now.</div>
