      <div class="sofi-reason"><strong>Member Growth:</strong> Management expects to add 3+ million new members in 2025 alone — that's 30% growth in one year. More members = more products sold = more revenue.</div>
      <div class="sofi-reason"><strong>Interest Rate Tailwind:</strong> Analysts expect interest rate cuts to benefit SoFi's lending business significantly. Lower rates = more people borrow = SoFi makes more loans.</div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted);margin-top:1.25rem;max-width:78vw;">We are not predicting the stock will rise. We don't need it to. We are selling puts below the current price — we just need SOFI to not collapse. A growing, profitable company with a banking license and 10M+ members is a reasonable business to back.</p>
