  <div class="slide slide-inspiration" data-week="0">
    <div class="i-eyebrow">// Who Did This Before You</div>
    <h2>People who looked like you<br>and built empires anyway.</h2>
    <div class="person-card" style="max-width:70vw;border-left-color:var(--teal);">
      <p class="person-story" style="font-size:clamp(0.9rem,1.5vw,1.05rem);">
        The financial markets were not built with us in mind. For most of American history, Black people were locked out — legally, structurally, and socially — from the very systems that build generational wealth.<br><br>
        <strong>That has changed.</strong> And the people on the next four slides didn't wait for an invitation. They studied the rules, mastered them, and then rewrote what was possible. None of them started where they ended up. All of them started by learning exactly what you're learning right now.
