  <!-- INSPIRATION — LAUREN SIMMONS -->
  <div class="slide slide-inspiration" data-week="0">
    <div class="i-eyebrow">// Trailblazer 1 of 4 — Black Women in Finance</div>
    <h2>Lauren Simmons</h2>
    <div class="person-card teal">
      <div class="person-name">Lauren Simmons</div>
      <div class="person-title">Youngest Trader · NYSE · "The Wolfette of Wall Street"</div>
      <p class="person-story">
        Lauren grew up in Marietta, Georgia. Her degree was in <strong>genetics</strong> — not finance. She had never worked in a bank. She had no connections on Wall Street. In 2017, at 22 years old, through sheer persistence and the willingness to learn anything fast, she walked onto the floor of the New York Stock Exchange and <strong>became the youngest full-time female equity trader in NYSE history</strong> — and only the second Black woman to ever hold that position in the exchange's 228-year history.<br><br>
        She went from knowing nothing about trading to moving <strong>$150 million a day</strong>. When asked how, she said: "I don't believe in failure. If it doesn't work out, shrug your shoulders and move forward."
